w.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bonnie-Wright-800x549.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bonnie-Wright-696x477.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bonnie-Wright-1392x955.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Bonnie-Wright-1068x732.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2030px) 100vw, 2030px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/harry-potter"><em>《哈利·波特》</em></a>主演邦妮·赖特表示，她对自己在电影中“被削减”的放映时间感到“失望”。</p><p> The actor played Ginny Weasley in the eight-film saga, growing from Ron&#39;s timid little sister to a confident young witch — and the eventual wife of Daniel Radcliffe&#39;s Harry Potter.</p><p> However, during an appearance on Michael Rosenbaum&#39;s <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KqOW45wD2a8&amp;pp=ygUfaW5zaWRlIG9mIHlvdSBtaWNoYWVsIHJvc2VuYmF1bQ%3D%3D" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Inside of You</em> podcast</a> , Wright said there could have been much more character development for Ginny had the writers stuck closer to JK Rowling&#39;s books.</p><p> During the chat, Wright explained how she felt anxious and frustrated while performing as Ginny, fearing that fans would react negatively if the character wasn&#39;t done justice. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="BONNIE WRIGHT: Growing Up Ginny Weasley, Harry Potter’s Next Generation &amp; Sharing Vulnerability" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/KqOW45wD2a8?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> “I definitely feel there was anxiety toward performing and doing the best thing as my character built, for instance,” she said. “Like, &#39;Oh gosh, will I do justice to this character that people love?&#39;</p><p> “So that was always hard to do, especially when, inevitably, a lot of the scenes of every character were chopped down from the book to the film. So you didn&#39;t really have as much to show in the film.”</p><p> She added: “Sometimes that was a little disappointing because there were parts of the character that just didn&#39;t get to come through because there weren&#39;t the scenes to do that,” she continued. “That made me feel a bit anxious or just frustrated, I guess.” </p><figure id="attachment_2564394" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-2564394" style="width: 2048px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-2564394" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/weasley-family.jpg" alt="Harry Potter's Weasley family" width="2048" height="1366" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/weasley-family.jpg 2048w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/weasley-family-696x464.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/weasley-family-1392x928.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/weasley-family-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/weasley-family-800x534.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/weasley-family-1068x712.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2048px) 100vw, 2048px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-2564394" class="wp-caption-text"> Fred, Ginny, George, and Ron Weasley in Harry Potter. Credit: Warner Bros.</figcaption></figure><p> Wright went to say to that there were “a million executives” who were in charge of the scripts and adapting the books, and that it was difficult to raise any of her concerns about her screen time. However, she eventually made peace with the fact that it was beyond her control.</p><p> “When fans do share that disappointment and they do it in a way that is like, &#39;We know it wasn&#39;t you. We just wanted more of you&#39;,” she said. “And that&#39;s the same of every character. If only they could be five-hour-long movies.”</p><p> Coincidentally, fans may soon get to spend a lot more time with Ginny as <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/harry-potter-tv-series-officially-confirmed-at-hbo-3429311">a <em>Harry Potter</em> TV series is currently in the works</a> at Max (formerly HBO Max), and promises to be a faithful adaptation of the books.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/harry-potter-ginny-weasley-actress-disappointed-with-chopped-down-screen-time-3491656">&#39;Harry Potter&#39; Ginny Weasley actress “disappointed” with “chopped down” screen time</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
